    <div class="container">
        <section id="about">
            <h2>About the Research</h2>
            <p>Our research team at Kings College London, Department of Nutritional Sciences, is conducting a study on Patient and Public Involvement and Engagement (PPIE) in healthcare research. We believe that involving patients and the public in research design and implementation leads to better outcomes and more relevant findings.</p>
            <p>This project aims to understand how patient perspectives can be better integrated into clinical research protocols, ultimately improving healthcare delivery and patient experiences.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section id="why-participate">
            <h2>Why Your Participation Matters</h2>
            <p>By participating in this research, you will:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Help researchers understand real patient experiences</li>
                <li>Contribute to improving healthcare services</li>
                <li>Ensure research addresses priorities that matter to patients</li>
                <li>Have your voice heard in the development of new healthcare approaches</li>
                <li>Learn about the research process and gain new skills</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We're looking for people from all backgrounds and experiences. You don't need any prior knowledge about research to participate.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section id="what-involved">
            <h2>What's Involved</h2>
            <p>Participation may include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Attending online or in-person discussion groups (approximately 1-2 hours)</li>
                <li>Reviewing research materials and providing feedback</li>
                <li>Completing short surveys about your experiences</li>
                <li>Participating in interviews with researchers</li>
            </ul>
            <p>All activities will be scheduled at convenient times, and we offer compensation for your time and expertise.</p>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Form Section - Embedded Tally Form -->
